definition: a row/a line/to set in order/to arrange/to line up/to eliminate/to drain/to push open/platoon/raft/classifier for lines, rows etc
to set/to fix/to determine/to decide/to order

sentences.english: The Task Scheduler schedules and coordinates tasks at run time.
sentences.chinese: 工作排程器可在执行阶段排定和协调工作。

sentences.english: The maiden voyage of the new ship is scheduled to start this afternoon.
sentences.chinese: 那艘新船的处女航被排定在今天下午开始。

sentences.english: The distance between the tower and the first row heliostats in tower SPPs is deduced.
sentences.chinese: 确定了镜场中第一排定日镜相对于接收塔的最佳距离。

sentences.english: I was scheduled to serve as day manager for the public tours of the house.
sentences.chinese: 我被排定担任负责白天公众参观的经理。

sentences.english: The President's speech is scheduled on next Friday.
sentences.chinese: 总统的演说排定在下礼拜五。

sentences.english: Please enable task scheduler service for scheduled job to fucntion.
sentences.chinese: 请启用任务计划程序服务以便执行排定计划的作业。

sentences.english: He'll probably have jetlag, so nothing's scheduled today.
sentences.chinese: 他可能还没适应时差，所以今天没有排定任何节目。

sentences.english: We've got our work cut out for us, but it'll happen.
sentences.chinese: 我们的工作已经排定了，它会发生的。

sentences.english: That vote hasn’t yet been scheduled.
sentences.chinese: 针对该法案的表决日期还尚未排定。

sentences.english: List of speakers for the general debate in the plenary shall be established on a first-come, first-served basis.
sentences.chinese: 全会一般性辩论的发言名单按先来后到顺序排定。

sentences.english: Boston's Terry Francona, scheduled to manage the AL team, mysteriously disappears in the Bronx hours before the game.
sentences.chinese: 原本排定的红袜队教练粉柯南，在赛前神秘失踪。

definition: to determine/to fix upon/to set (a target, a price etc)
to lay down (a rule, a plan of action)/to draw up/booked out (i.e. already fully booked)
to arrange (shifts, runs, classes etc) in order
to substitute/to complement in the proper order/to fill vacancies progressively
to consider and decide/to decide after investigating
to assign (a task to different people)/to allocate
the 12 earthly branches 子[zi3], 丑, 寅, 卯, 辰, 巳, 午, 未, 申, 酉, 戌, 亥 (used cyclically in the calendar and as ordinal number)
to arrange in order/to compile/to prepare (a budget, project etc)
to check up on sb's achievements
